Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.02,0:00:04.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Encounters are mysterious!\NBut the world is even more so!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.31,0:00:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad I'm with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.52,0:00:09.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's an author mystery!\NSome mysteries exist outside of writing!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.19,0:00:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.74,0:00:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.78,0:00:15.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.01,0:01:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Mystery Writer\NDisappearance Case (Part 1).
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.15,0:02:16.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, Matsuda Samonji, have solved\Ntonight's bloody string of murders!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.57,0:02:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That person is undoubtedly the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.61,0:02:22.07,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Samonji
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.54,0:02:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The son! The son! The son did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.38,0:02:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's dumb! The son is a fake!\NIt's the wife of the murdered man!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.55,0:02:39.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think did it,\NConan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.80,0:02:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll say the same person as you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.51,0:02:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See! Even he thinks so!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.93,0:02:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How would he know?\NKids don't know anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.48,0:02:55.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.48,0:03:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is you, his son!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.70,0:03:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.07,0:03:04.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.28,0:03:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was different the last time I saw it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.83,0:03:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective Samonji\Nseries is always being remade,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.21,0:03:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the killer changes each time!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.33,0:03:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it's always so interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.88,0:03:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You blockhead!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.97,0:03:25.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that for?!\NDon't make me mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.55,0:03:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.56,0:03:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, Dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.35,0:03:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quick-draw detective,\Nmy butt! How pathetic!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.27,0:03:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn it back! Samonji's about to\Npull out his sword and say a haiku!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.07,0:03:41.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.15,0:03:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! Turn it back!\NIt's going to end!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.33,0:03:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Things sure are peaceful for\Nfather and daughter to argue over this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.75,0:03:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So many people have fallen\Nvictim to their organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.13,0:04:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But nobody realizes it's\Nthe organization's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.76,0:04:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I want to be normal again,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.05,0:04:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to turn this bumbling\Ndetective into a real master detective
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.01,0:04:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and obtain information on the\Nmen in black's organization!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.39,0:04:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he gets more work, I'll eventually\Nrun into a case involving them!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.28,0:04:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I continue to seek\Nthe truth, I know I can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.45,0:04:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's over!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.33,0:04:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so good about it anyway?\NHe's just a third-rate detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.58,0:04:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So says the dimwitted detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.59,0:04:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, the original\Nseries ended long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.18,0:04:47.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's annoying that\Nthey keep putting it on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.97,0:04:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, they started the serials again!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.27,0:04:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see. I'm sure it's around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.69,0:04:59.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Literature Era {\i0}started it two months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.98,0:05:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.98,0:05:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Shinmei Nintaro's highly\Nanticipated 'Detective Samonji' returns!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.74,0:05:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.20,0:05:12.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This takes me back!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.12,0:05:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He and a killer disappeared\Ninto a fire ten years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.16,0:05:17.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I guess he survived!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.42,0:05:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It takes you back?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.42,0:05:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what Shinichi-{\i1}niichan\N{\i0}said on the phone the other day...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.42,0:05:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi did?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.38,0:05:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That mystery nerd, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.98,0:05:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? I think someone's\Nat your office downstairs...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.65,0:05:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, tell them it's late\Nand to come back tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.94,0:05:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.70,0:05:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! The office is closed for the day!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.37,0:05:57.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I really do need to talk\Nto Detective Mori about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.21,0:06:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could he at least hear what I have to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.05,0:06:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hottie!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.92,0:06:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's rather late, so could\Nyou come back tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.39,0:06:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, wait, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.10,0:06:15.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying to our guest?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.27,0:06:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to keep you waiting!\NI am Mori Kogoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.90,0:06:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for my rude daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.23,0:06:28.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please! Come right in!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.15,0:06:28.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.99,0:06:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.91,0:06:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that attitude?\NYou told me to turn her away!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.50,0:06:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, have a seat!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.92,0:06:47.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies! Go right ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.34,0:06:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.72,0:06:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing special, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.43,0:06:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.94,0:07:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then.\NMay I ask what brings you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.19,0:07:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. My name is Shinmei Kaori.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.44,0:07:10.45,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinmei Kaori
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.44,0:07:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. My name is Shinmei Kaori.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.99,0:07:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinmei? You don't mean--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.95,0:07:14.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mystery writer's--?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.41,0:07:17.95,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinmei Kaori (22), office worker
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.41,0:07:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Shinmei Nintaro is my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.08,0:07:22.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the daughter\Nof that great master?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.00,0:07:27.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can never get enough of\NSamonji's haikus!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.63,0:07:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.59,0:07:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how can I help you?\NDoes he want to use me in a novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.64,0:07:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, actually... my father\Nhas been missing for two months.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.10,0:07:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.31,0:07:44.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...missing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.48,0:07:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is quite--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.86,0:07:48.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be silly!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.73,0:07:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been writing serials for\N{\i1}Literature Era {\i0}for the past two months!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.03,0:07:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's the truth! He and my mother\Ndisappeared from their home!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.03,0:07:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Your mother, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.00,0:08:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They both vanished about one\Nweek before this serialization began.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.96,0:08:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I checked with all our relatives\Nand acquaintances of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.97,0:08:15.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but no one knew anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.43,0:08:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, don't his serials mean\Nthat he is writing manuscripts?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.81,0:08:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.06,0:08:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oddly enough, the manuscripts\Nare faxed to the editing department.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.73,0:08:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every Saturday, at exactly midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.16,0:08:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't the faxes have the\Nsender's phone number or anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.50,0:08:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.96,0:08:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems the sender has it configured\Nnot to display those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.88,0:08:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.96,0:08:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably because he and\Nhis wife are on vacation somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.51,0:08:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he sends the faxes\Nfrom the hotel they're staying at!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.26,0:09:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so too at first!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.64,0:09:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they've never been\Nquiet for two months like this before!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.90,0:09:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can only think that something happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.61,0:09:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you contact the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.40,0:09:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.70,0:09:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked them to investigate,\Nbut there had been no ransom calls
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.49,0:09:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the manuscripts were\Nbeing sent, so they said not to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.25,0:09:31.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tried the other detective agencies,\Nbut they all said the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.88,0:09:39.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're my last hope, Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.39,0:09:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is pointless!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.56,0:09:46.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're only wasting time by sitting here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.77,0:09:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's check the editing department\Nwhere his manuscripts get sent!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.36,0:09:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can save your\Ntroubles for after that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.82,0:09:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.99,0:10:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taxi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.67,0:10:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.64,0:10:26.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Shinmei-{\i1}sensei{\i0}'s manuscripts get sent here every week.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.97,0:10:26.81,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Daigakukan
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.18,0:10:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More should be sent today,\Nat any time now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.48,0:10:36.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are these manuscripts\Nreally written by him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.19,0:10:42.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Although they're typed out,\Nthe words are most definitely his!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.37,0:10:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He signs his name next\Nto the title each time, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.79,0:10:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can show you the faxed\Nmanuscripts, if you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.37,0:10:55.34,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Halves at the Top
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.05,0:10:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The title is "Halves at the Top"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.18,0:11:02.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he's signed them, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.10,0:11:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you certain this is his signature?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.27,0:11:13.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. We confirmed it\Nwhen I came here earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.52,0:11:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing\Nto worry about, Kaori-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.82,0:11:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he's just so focused\Non writing that he forgot to contact you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.57,0:11:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The same thing happens\Nto lots of other writers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.12,0:11:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But are you sure he forgot?\NHis wife's with him...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.58,0:11:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.59,0:11:40.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he seem different in any way?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.92,0:11:42.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Different?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.22,0:11:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, like during\Na meeting or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.05,0:11:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we had a simple meeting\Nbefore we started the serials,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.68,0:11:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he didn't seem any different...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.81,0:11:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything at all?\NEven the tiniest thing might help...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.94,0:12:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose there is the fact he\Nrestarted his Detective Samonji series.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.03,0:12:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.49,0:12:14.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see, I have been asking him\Nto restart this series for the past four years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.29,0:12:17.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he always answered by saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.17,0:12:22.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Samonji is dead.\NThere's no bringing him back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.47,0:12:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I had half given up when\Nhe suddenly called two months ago
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.05,0:12:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to ask if we could make\Nroom for his new Samonji series.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.48,0:12:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were more than\Nhappy to oblige, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.48,0:12:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we hurriedly canceled\Nthe new series we were running
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.49,0:12:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and replaced it with Samonji.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.78,0:12:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.24,0:12:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come to think of it,\Nthis doesn't pertain to him exactly,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.21,0:12:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but for the dedication, he wrote this:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.79,0:13:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Attention, all master\Ndetectives throughout Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.92,0:13:07.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you wish to surpass my intellect,\Nsolve this case's true mystery."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.18,0:13:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite a provocative dedication.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.51,0:13:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. And ever since the\Nfirst chapter, we've received
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.52,0:13:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,tons of calls and fan letters saying,\N"This is how it was done!"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.65,0:13:22.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As an editor, it makes me happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.40,0:13:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it seemed like a rare move\Nfor such a mild-mannered writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.45,0:13:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, fans have been waiting\Nlike crazy for over ten years,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.74,0:13:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so it's only natural he's\Ngetting such a big reception.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.58,0:13:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Like crazy"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.96,0:13:41.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there was even a scary\Ncall last year from a crazed fan
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.29,0:13:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who threatened to set this place\Non fire if he didn't restart the series!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.18,0:13:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about extreme...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.47,0:13:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes! There's one\Nother thing that seemed strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.52,0:13:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He appears in his own novel!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.48,0:13:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.90,0:14:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinmei-{\i1}sensei {\i0}appears in the story,\Nas an old friend of Samonji's!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.78,0:14:08.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a struggling\Nwriter who resides in France.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.32,0:14:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are about forty stories in\Nthe series, but this is a first!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.16,0:14:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's going to end\Nwith all the previous cases
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.25,0:14:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,being things Samonji told him about!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.25,0:14:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kind of like how\NWatson is to Sherlock Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.59,0:14:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say! Could you show me that scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.18,0:14:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.10,0:14:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But can you read kanji, little boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.93,0:14:39.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A little!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.90,0:14:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're right! Here he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.86,0:14:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinmei-{\i1}sensei {\i0}makes his first appearance
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.11,0:14:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when Samonji calls a friend living\Nin France for advice on a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.49,0:14:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His character is absentminded and funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.87,0:15:00.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.00,0:15:06.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.38,0:15:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.67,0:15:10.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.47,0:15:14.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,10:00 is written in kanji here,\Nbut 1:00 is written with a number!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.47,0:15:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This guy must've been pretty tired, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.10,0:15:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is strange. Could this actually be...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.94,0:15:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a misprint on your part?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.61,0:15:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.49,0:15:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We wanted to fix it to\Nmake it easier to read, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.03,0:15:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he said, "The lay of the letters\Nis a novel's life! Don't change it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.50,0:15:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said it many times before the serialization.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.17,0:15:51.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He also said he'd cancel the\Nseries immediately if we defied his wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then that makes it all the odder.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.30,0:15:59.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost as if something\Nis being hidden in the writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.85,0:16:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then there are\NShinmei-{\i1}sensei{\i0}'s signatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.31,0:16:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If my theory is correct,\Nit's possible that he's already...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.36,0:16:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Here's his latest fax!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.41,0:16:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see here...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.08,0:16:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't look yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.33,0:16:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a mystery story!\NWait until it's in book form to read it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.55,0:16:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.72,0:16:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.72,0:16:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.43,0:16:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But his signature is weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.89,0:16:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chapters six through eight match perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.19,0:16:51.48,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Nintaro
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.86,0:16:53.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-They do!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.90,0:16:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chapters one through six are all\Nslightly different, though. I wonder why!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.49,0:17:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He obviously just\Ncopied an earlier signature.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.50,0:17:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.33,0:17:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he didn't\Nwant to write it anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.75,0:17:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...or he couldn't anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.46,0:17:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.76,0:17:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he can't write anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.22,0:17:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that means Shinmei-{\i1}sensei\N{\i0}might already be dead, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.26,0:17:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.76,0:17:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad! This\Nrequires immediate action!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.60,0:17:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You! The police! Call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.15,0:17:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.36,0:17:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not 100% yet!\NThere's a chance he's still alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.36,0:17:43.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The key to saving his life is\Nprobably hidden inside this novel!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.16,0:17:48.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a message he's left for us detectives!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.25,0:17:51.46,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Daigakukan
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.30,0:17:54.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't open an investigation?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.88,0:17:59.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we still can't. Not at this stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.84,0:18:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.97,0:18:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinmei Nintaro,\Nher father and a mystery writer,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.19,0:18:11.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has been missing for two months now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.73,0:18:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, his wife is also gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.44,0:18:19.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can only think they got\Ncaught up in some sort of incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.28,0:18:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, his manuscripts are\Nbeing faxed here every single week.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.38,0:18:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though they're faxes,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.96,0:18:38.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,his daughter and the editors\Nall agree it's his writing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.05,0:18:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And like I said, those\Nfaxes are the issue here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.51,0:18:46.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't those signatures\Nseem strange to you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.23,0:18:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Signatures? But they were\Nalready confirmed to be his.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.73,0:19:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Between Chapter one and six,\Nhis signatures are all slightly different,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.70,0:19:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but between Chapter six and eight,\Nthey're all exactly the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.03,0:19:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're obviously copies\Nof a previous signature
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.70,0:19:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and evidence that he's now in\Na condition in which he can't write!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.42,0:19:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,\Nsomething has happened to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.38,0:19:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then tell me...\NWho did what to Mr. Shinmei?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.84,0:19:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd believe you more if there\Nwas a threatening phone call,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.68,0:19:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's been nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.89,0:19:36.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, maybe he got sick of\Nsigning them and used copies instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.02,0:19:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True. Given the circumstances,\NInspector Megure is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.61,0:19:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't be surprising\Nfor an eccentric writer
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.62,0:19:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to take his wife and hole up\Nsomewhere to focus on his writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.75,0:19:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But something bugs me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.08,0:20:03.68,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Attention, all master detectives throughout\NJapan!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.75,0:19:57.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't like him to write that dedication.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.25,0:20:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was very extreme and provocative\Nfor someone so mild-mannered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.68,0:20:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, there's the fact the writer\Nsuddenly appears in the series.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.77,0:20:13.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then there's his odd dialogue
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.69,0:20:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that mixes numbers, kanji\Nnumbers, and English letters...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.61,0:20:22.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If my theory is correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.70,0:20:27.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there must be a message\Nfrom Shinmei-{\i1}sensei {\i0}in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.37,0:20:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector! I made copies of all\Nthe lines Mori-{\i1}san {\i0}was curious about.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.88,0:20:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Shinmei makes\Nfour appearances so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.96,0:20:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I have a copy, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.76,0:20:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that! Don't get in the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.35,0:20:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay! There are extras!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.64,0:20:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.47,0:20:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.64,0:20:57.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, his first appearance\Nis when the main detective character
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.65,0:21:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,calls Mr. Shinmei,\Nwho is residing in France.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.40,0:21:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's also in France the second time...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.32,0:21:08.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in France the third time...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.78,0:21:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the fourth time, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.16,0:21:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does Mr. Shinmei like France?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.00,0:21:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He and my mother\Noften traveled there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.50,0:21:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! Reading them backwards\Nor rearranging them doesn't work!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.26,0:21:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only I had a point to start from!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.97,0:21:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, do you mind if we use\NChapter eight of "Halves at the Top,"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.68,0:21:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the manuscript he just faxed?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.56,0:21:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Halves at the top?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.35,0:21:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the title of the work\Nyou're reading right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.07,0:21:45.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Halves at the--?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.53,0:21:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Halves at the top?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.53,0:21:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, now!\NCould this actually be--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.88,0:22:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-This is--!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.21,0:22:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.88,0:22:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a message from\NShinmei-{\i1}sensei {\i0}hidden in these lines!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.18,0:22:14.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which makes it all fit:\Nthat provocative dedication,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.89,0:22:18.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the author's appearance in the story,\Nand the odd lines of dialogue!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.15,0:22:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what is the goal of the person\Nholding him and his wife captive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.97,0:24:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.66,0:24:05.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Takagi-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.39,0:24:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this manuscript!\NThere's more dialogue!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.74,0:24:13.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? This is the eighth\Nchapter that was just faxed here?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.50,0:24:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Hurry..."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.96,0:24:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"There's..."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.50,0:24:18.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"...no time..."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.83,0:24:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Hurry, there's no time!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.01,0:24:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.48,0:24:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Mystery Writer\NDisappearance Case (Part 2)."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.23,0:24:50.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.15,0:24:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,French language.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.88,0:24:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Message from author Aoyama-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.19,0:24:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd he say? That he likes this segment?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.70,0:24:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
